 granted to an employee by any wage law in the State. Provides that it is a violation of the Act for an employer to accept a referral of an individual for employment from an employment agency not licensed under the Act. Eliminates criminal penalties; provides civil penalties for both employment agencies and employers for violating the Act. Provides that all fees and civil penalties collected under the Act shall be deposited into the Wage Theft Enforcement Fund.", "pending_committee_id": 0, "committee": [], "referrals": [{"date": "2015-02-20", "committee_id": 254, "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 36, "name": "Assignments"}, {"date": "2015-03-11", "committee_id": 278, "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 36, "name": "Labor"}, {"date": "2015-04-23", "committee_id": 235, "chamber": "H", "chamber_id": 35, "name": "Rules"}, {"date": "2015-05-04", "committee_id": 2892, "chamber": "H", "chamber_id": 35, "name": "Labor & Commerce"}], "history": [{"date": "2015-02-20", "action": "Filed with Secretary by Sen. Linda Holmes", "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 36, "importance": 1}, {"date": "2015-02-20", "action": "First Reading", "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 36, "importance": 0}, {"date": "2015-02-20", "action": "Referred to Assignments", "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 36, "importance": 1}, {"date": "2015-03-11", "action": "Assigned to Labor", "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 36, "importance": 1}, {"date": "2015-03-18", "action": "Postponed - Labor", "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 36, "importance": 0}, {"date": "2015-03-25", "action": "Do Pass Labor; 010-001-000", "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 36, "importance": 1}, {"date": "2015-03-25", "action": "Placed on Calendar Order of 2nd Reading March 26, 2015", "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 36, "importance": 0}, {"date": "2015-04-17", "action": "Senate Floor Amendment No. 1 Filed with Secretary by Sen. Linda Holmes", "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 36, "importance": 0}, {"date": "2015-04-17", "action": "Senate Floor Amendment No. 1 Referred to Assignments